  "text": "One example of how this reciprocity plays out currently is the relationship among bears and people in the Kitasoo/Xai'xais Nation, which owns and runs the Spirit Bear Lodge, a communityled ecotourism business named after the Spirit Bear, a whitecoated black bear that occurs in the region. The growth of this Ecology and Society 23(3): 35 https://www.ecologyandsociety.org/vol23/iss3/art35/ company has resulted in substantial benefits for the community, including improving employment and supporting cultural resurgence [CITATION_1] Douglas Neasloss 2016, personal communication) . In turn, the organization contributes to multifaceted, region-wide conservation efforts, including support of the Spirit Bear Research Foundation, which facilitates research on the conservation and ecology of bears throughout the territory and raises awareness of their importance (see https:// spiritbearfoundation.com).",
